udo champion Shohei Ono of Japan, French sprinter Bruno Marie-Rose, Brazilian football player Souza Vieira de Oliveira and France men's football national team coach Didier Deschamps.\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shohei_Ono\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shohei Ono\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shohei_Ono\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shohei_Ono\"}, {\"begin\": 670, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.7058663764172558, \"rank\": 0.4135185215421469, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruno_Marie-Rose\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bruno Marie-Rose\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruno_Marie-Rose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruno_Marie-Rose\"}, {\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9977716678652588, \"rank\": 0.002233302651570859, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Didier_Deschamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Didier Deschamps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Didier_Deschamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Didier_Deschamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French tennis player Caroline Garcia was the day's final torchbearer and she lit the cauldron at the historic celebration venue in Versailles.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"en